bson_append_date_time(): precondition failed: value
$res[0] = bless( {
         'value' => '5459d0ed9138487d7d125101'
       }, 'MongoDB::OID' )
{code}
...I get the error.

The following line in MongoDB::Collection::aggregate assumes that database names can be matched by \w+:

{code}
$ns =~ s{^\w+\.}{}
{code}

There are valid database names, however, that do not match \w+. The consequence in the case of such a database is that the collection returned by aggregate (if outputNs is specified) will have the wrong name. Subsequent queries against this collection will then fail silently by returning no results, because the namespace does not actually exist.
